@feric-isc I wonder if name of the debug file was correct for your `libmonosgen-2.0.so`. There's a section in the ELF file, named `.gnu_debuglink`, which contains the expected name of the debug data file. You can check what it is by running `llvm-readelf --string-dump=.gnu_debuglink libmonosgen-2.0.so`

Also, `ndk-stack` might not have been able to recognize the stack trace format, it might be expecting the Android system crash report format. However, your stack traces are in a format that could be easily read by a shell script and then
fed to `llvm-addr2line`. Use this invocation of the utility: `llvm-addr2line -paCif -e libmonosgen-2.0.so <ADDRESS>`

